 <div class="section-title">Your Role as Greeter</div>
 <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;color:var(--text-muted)">The greeter is the first point of contact for participants. Your job is to welcome them warmly, verify their identity, explain the process, and route them to the appropriate screening stations. A smooth greeter experience sets the tone for the entire event.</p>

 <h3 class="sub">Event Flow — Step by Step</h3>
 <ol class="sop-list">
 <li>Greet the participant with a smile, locate their appointment in Salesforce, and verify their full name and date of birth. If no appointment, determine best opportunity for them to participate today without disrupting confirmed appointments. The greeter will also manage the queue.</li>
 <li>Write participant's name on bottom of result form.</li>
 <li>Perform height and weight and capture reading on paper result form. (See height wand training and video)</li>
 <li>Direct the participant to next available screener.</li>
 </ol>

 <div class="section-title">Setup &amp; Dress</div>
 <p style="margin:0 0 4px 0"><strong>Dress code:</strong> Plain black scrubs (pants and top), closed toed shoes, socks, no other healthcare company brands visible.</p>
 <p style="margin:0 0 6px 0"><strong>Setup:</strong></p>
 <ul class="bullet-list">
 <li>See setup duration in USW GO app.</li>
 <li>Greeter station near front entrance.</li>
 <li>Clean, organized workspace.</li>
 <li>Boxes tucked under tables.</li>
 </ul>

 <div class="callout info">
 <span class="callout-icon">ℹ️</span>
 <div><strong>Privacy reminder</strong> At all stations, never say a participant's result aloud. Point to the recorded value on the results form. All biometric results are Protected Health Information (PHI).</div>
 </div>

