 <!-- MODULE 3: CARDIOCHEK -->
 <div class="page" id="page-mod4">
 <div class="module-header">
 <div class="module-tag">Module 04</div>
 <h2>CardioChek Plus</h2>
 <div class="desc">Lipid panel and glucose testing — optics check, SOP, and troubleshooting for the CardioChek Plus v1.12.</div>
 </div>

 <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:16px">The CardioChek Plus measures total cholesterol, HDL, triglycerides, and glucose from a single fingerstick, delivering results in approximately 90 seconds. It also calculates LDL, TC/HDL ratio, LDL/HDL ratio, and non-HDL cholesterol.</p>

 <div class="callout warn">
 <span class="callout-icon">⚠️</span>
 <div><strong>Optics check required before every event</strong> Must also be performed every time the machine is moved or dropped, or if there is a dramatic temperature change in the testing environment.</div>
 </div>

 <div class="section-title">Before You Begin</div>
 <ul class="bullet-list">
 <li>Ensure 4 AA 1.5V batteries are installed.</li>
 <li>Have the grey check strip (in the black case) ready.</li>
 <li>Do <strong>not</strong> insert the MEMO chip when running the optics check.</li>
 <li>MEMO chip lot number must match the lot number on your strips.</li>
 <li>Do <strong>not</strong> store the MEMO chip in the vial with the CardioChek strips — it is magnetized and will contaminate them.</li>
 </ul>

 <div class="section-title">Optics Check (Check Strip Verification)</div>
 <ol class="sop-list">
 <li>Turn the CardioChek Plus on by pressing the ON/Enter button.</li>
 <li>When "INSTALL MEMO CHIP or RUN TEST" appears, press the Next button until "CHECK STRIP" is displayed.</li>
 <li>Press ENTER when CHECK STRIP is displayed.</li>
 <li>Hold the grey check strip at the base (ribbed side up) and insert into the reflectance test strip slot (large slot, lower center) when "INSERT STRIP" is displayed.</li>
 <li>The analyzer should display <strong>PASSED</strong> with a checkmark icon. Remove the strip and return it to the black case. Log results in Salesforce (or the US Wellness Optics Check Log for paper events).</li>
 <li>Press NEXT until EXIT is displayed. Press ENTER.</li>
 <li>Press NEXT until RUN TEST is displayed. Press ENTER. Analyzer is now ready.</li>
 </ol>

 <div class="callout danger">
 <span class="callout-icon">🚨</span>
 <div><strong>If FAILED appears:</strong> Clean the test strip slot, inspect the check strip for damage, and retry. If it fails a second time, do not use the device on any participant — call <strong>866.881.7607</strong> immediately.</div>
 </div>

 <div class="section-title">Running a Lipid + Glucose Test</div>
 <ol class="sop-list">
 <li>Turn on CardioChek Plus. Confirm optics check has passed.</li>
 <li>Insert the correct MEMO chip (finger notch side up, lot number code facing down). Confirm MEMO chip lot matches your strips.</li>
 <li>As the participant sits down, sanitize hands and apply latex-free gloves.</li>
 <li>Prepare supplies: remove one test strip from the vial, blood collection tube, alcohol swab, gauze, and bandage. Recap the vial immediately — strips must not be exposed more than 6–8 minutes.</li>
 <li>Insert glucose strip into the small slot (lower right) of the CardioChek. Obtain a blood drop via fingerstick. Gently hold the finger to the mouth of the glucose strip. The mouth is the opening on the short edge of the strip. Do not put blood on the top of the strip.</li>
 <li>Insert lipid strip into the large slot on the lower center of the CardioChek body. Ensure the clear window of the strip is in the uppermost portion of the slot (push all the way up). Strips not inserted all the way or inserted backwards will yield an inaccurate reading of 400 Total Cholesterol and 100 HDL.</li>
 <li>Wipe the finger with gauze. Obtain a fresh blood drop and collect with the pipette.</li>
 <li>When the pipette is full, apply the sample to the test strip window. Results appear in about 90 seconds.</li>
 <li>The Reflectance and Electrochemical icons will display together. To skip glucose, press and hold NEXT until the analyzer strikes out GLU.</li>
 <li>Wipe excess blood from the participant's finger. Have them apply pressure with gauze, then apply a bandage.</li>
 <li>Toggle through results with the arrow button. Record in Salesforce (or paper form).</li>
 <li>Discard all blood-contact materials into the Sharps container. Disinfect and wipe down the machine.</li>
 </ol>

 <div class="do-dont">
 <div class="do-box">
 <h5>✓ DO</h5>
 <ul>
 <li>Recap test vial immediately after removing a single strip</li>
 <li>Follow machine prompts — insert and apply only when prompted</li>
 <li>Confirm MEMO chip lot matches strips</li>
 <li>Log QC results in Salesforce after every event</li>
 </ul>
 </div>
 <div class="dont-box">
 <h5>✗ DON'T</h5>
 <ul>
 <li>Lay strips out ahead of time (exposure &gt; 6–8 min = inaccurate results)</li>
 <li>Store strips in a car or non-temperature-controlled area</li>
 <li>Store the MEMO chip in the strip vial</li>
 <li>Apply sample before the machine says "Apply Sample"</li>
 </ul>
 </div>
 </div>

 <div class="section-title">FAQ — N/A Results</div>
 <div class="info-card" style="margin-bottom:12px">
 <div class="card-title">Why does LDL show N/A?</div>
 <p>N/A is not an error. LDL is calculated from TC, HDL, and Triglycerides. If any of those values fall outside the system's reference range (displaying &lt; or &gt;), LDL and TC/HDL ratio will show N/A. Record the result as displayed.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="info-card">
 <div class="card-title">When to retest</div>
 <p>Retest if TC is &lt;100 or &gt;400 — this likely indicates an error. Most other &lt; or &gt; values are accurate readings and should be recorded as shown.</p>
 </div>

 <div class="section-title">Common Error Codes</div>
 <div class="troubleshoot-row"><div class="err">MEMO CHIP ERROR</div><div class="cause">MEMO chip is defective</div><div class="fix">Use another MEMO chip from the same lot</div></div>
 <div class="troubleshoot-row"><div class="err">TEST NOT ALLOWED</div><div class="cause">Test selected by MEMO chip cannot run on this analyzer</div><div class="fix">Check MEMO chip; call Customer Service if issue persists</div></div>
 <div class="troubleshoot-row"><div class="err">EXPIRED LOT</div><div class="cause">Strips expired, wrong MEMO chip, or date/time not set</div><div class="fix">Check strip expiration and MEMO chip; verify date/time setting</div></div>
 <div class="troubleshoot-row"><div class="err">TEST ERROR</div><div class="cause">Insufficient sample, wrong temperature, strip removed early, or eGLU error</div><div class="fix">Retest with a new strip; ensure correct sample volume and temperature</div></div>
 <div class="troubleshoot-row"><div class="err">E1: STRIP ERROR</div><div class="cause">eGLU strip damaged or lot numbers don't match</div><div class="fix">Retest with a new strip; confirm strip and MEMO chip lot numbers match</div></div>
 <div class="troubleshoot-row"><div class="err">E4: USED STRIP</div><div class="cause">eGLU strip has already been used</div><div class="fix">Use a new test strip</div></div>

