 <!-- MODULE 4: A1C -->
 <div class="page" id="page-mod5">
 <div class="module-header">
 <div class="module-tag">Module 05</div>
 <h2>Bayer A1c Now</h2>
 <div class="desc">A1c testing SOP, storage requirements, result interpretation, and counseling framework.</div>
 </div>

 <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:16px">The A1c test measures the average amount of glucose in the blood over the last 2–3 months (based on the 120-day lifespan of red blood cells). It is used both to monitor glucose control in diagnosed diabetics and as a screening tool for participants at higher risk of developing diabetes.</p>

 <div class="callout info">
 <span class="callout-icon">🎥</span>
 <div><strong>Required training video</strong> Watch the A1cNow+ training video at <strong>ptsdiagnostics.com/a1cnow-training/</strong> before your first event. Key chapters: Test Storage · Collecting Blood · Running the Test · Reading Results.</div>
 </div>

 <div class="section-title">Kit Contents &amp; Storage</div>
 <div class="two-col">
 <div class="info-card">
 <div class="card-title">Kit Contents</div>
 <ul class="bullet-list" style="margin-top:8px">
 <li>Analyzer</li>
 <li>Shaker body</li>
 <li>Blood collector</li>
 <li>Test cartridge (Pouch 2)</li>
 <li>Sample dilution pouch (Pouch 1)</li>
 </ul>
 </div>
 <div class="info-card">
 <div class="card-title">Storage Rules</div>
 <ul class="bullet-list" style="margin-top:8px">
 <li>Store refrigerated until expiration OR at room temperature up to 4 months</li>
 <li>Record date placed at room temp on box</li>
 <li>If refrigerated, allow ≥1 hour to reach room temp before use</li>
 <li>Keep out of direct sunlight</li>
 <li>Each analyzer may run up to 10 tests before disposal</li>
 </ul>
 </div>
 </div>

 <div class="section-title">Standard Operating Procedure</div>
 <ol class="sop-list">
 <li><strong>Review kit supplies.</strong> Confirm analyzer, shaker body, blood collector, and test cartridge are all present.</li>
 <li><strong>Confirm room temperature &amp; flat surface.</strong> All equipment must be at room temperature before testing begins.</li>
 <li><strong>Verify lot numbers match</strong> between the analyzer and Pouch 1 (sample dilution pouch). The test will error if they do not match.</li>
 <li><strong>Open Pouch 1</strong> (sample dilution pouch). <span style="color:var(--usw-danger);font-weight:600">DO NOT open Pouch 2 yet.</span></li>
 <li><strong>Perform fingerstick</strong> per USW standards. The same puncture site may be used if A1c and cholesterol tests are running concurrently.</li>
 <li><strong>Collect blood sample.</strong> Touch the blood drop to fill the blood collector — not too little, not too much.</li>
 <li><strong>Insert blood collector into shaker body</strong> (you should hear an audible click) and shake well 6–8 times.</li>
 <li><strong>Open Pouch 2</strong> and confirm the cartridge and analyzer codes match.</li>
 <li><strong>Insert cartridge into analyzer.</strong> Wait for SMPL to appear. Remove the base of the shaker body and push down firmly but gently into the analyzer well. Remove the shaker body quickly once the sample has been dispensed.</li>
 <li><strong>Do not move or handle the analyzer</strong> until the test is complete (~5 minutes). A countdown timer will appear. When complete: QCOK → result → remaining test count.</li>
 <li><strong>Record the result</strong> in Salesforce and on the paper results sheet.</li>
 <li><strong>Dispose of cartridge</strong> in the Sharps container. Save the analyzer — up to 10 tests per analyzer. Discard in regular trash after 10 tests.</li>
 </ol>

 <div class="callout danger">
 <span class="callout-icon">🚨</span>
 <div><strong>QCOK not displayed?</strong> Do NOT report the result. Call the on-call team immediately at <strong>866.881.7607</strong>.</div>
 </div>

 <div class="section-title">A1c Reference Ranges</div>
 <table class="ref-table">
 <thead><tr><th>A1c Value</th><th>Classification</th><th>Action</th></tr></thead>
