 <!-- MODULE 6: BAYER GLUCOMETER -->
 <div class="page" id="page-mod6">
 <div class="module-header">
 <div class="module-tag">Module 06</div>
 <h2>Bayer Contour Glucometer</h2>
 <div class="desc">Blood glucose screening using the Bayer Contour Meter — quality control, testing procedure, error codes, and result interpretation.</div>
 </div>

 <div class="callout warn">
 <span class="callout-icon">⚠️</span>
 <div><strong>When to use the Bayer Glucometer</strong> At events where the CardioChek is only performing <strong>Total Cholesterol</strong> or <strong>TC + HDL</strong> (not a full lipid panel), the Bayer Contour Glucometer is used to obtain the glucose reading rather than using an eGlu strip for CardioChek. <strong>Do not stick the participant twice.</strong></div>
 </div>

 <div class="section-title">Before You Begin — Quality Control</div>
 <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:10px">Quality control (QC) is performed by US Wellness prior to sending equipment to events. Allow the instrument and strips 20 minutes to adjust to the location. Check expiration and discard dates on all test strips and control solution — discard dates are 6 months after opening, and the earlier date always takes precedence.</p>
 <ol class="sop-list">
 <li>Clean hands with antibacterial wipes or sanitizer. Apply latex-free exam gloves.</li>
 <li>Check expiration and discard dates on the test strip container.</li>
 <li>Remove one test strip. Close the bottle lid immediately. Inspect the strip — discard if torn or damaged.</li>
 <li>Hold the strip with the <strong>gray end facing up</strong>. Insert the gray end into the test strip port. The meter will turn on and display a flashing blood drop when ready.</li>
 <li>Gently rock the control solution bottle before opening. Squeeze a small drop onto a clean, non-absorbent surface (blood barrier mat). Do not apply directly from the bottle to the strip.</li>
 <li>Immediately touch the <strong>tip</strong> of the test strip to the drop. Hold until the meter beeps. The meter will count down 5 seconds and display the result.</li>
 <li>A check mark appears on the display — this confirms it is a control result only. It does <em>not</em> mean the result is in range.</li>
 <li>Dispose of the test strip in the Sharps/biohazard container.</li>
 <li>Compare the result to the reference range on the bottom of the test strip box. Record QC time and results on the US Wellness QC Log.</li>
 <li>If any result is out of range, call USW at <strong>(866) 881-7607</strong> before testing any participants.</li>
 <li>Repeat steps 1–10 using the LOW control solution.</li>
 </ol>

 <div class="callout danger">
 <span class="callout-icon">🚫</span>
 <div><strong>No patient tests may be performed on an instrument that has failed QC.</strong> If controls are outside acceptable limits after corrective action, call US Wellness at <strong>(866) 881-7607</strong> and do not use the device.</div>
 </div>

 <div class="section-title">Testing Procedure</div>
 <ol class="sop-list">
 <li>Clean hands with antibacterial wipes or sanitizer. Apply fresh latex-free exam gloves for each participant.</li>
 <li>Check the expiration date on test strips. Remove one strip and close the bottle immediately.</li>
 <li>Hold the strip with the <strong>gray end facing up</strong>. Insert the gray end into the test strip port. The meter turns on — wait for the flashing blood drop.</li>
 <li>Select the side of a center finger of either hand. Hands should be warm to promote blood flow.</li>
 <li>Clean the fingertip with an alcohol swab and dry thoroughly with gauze.</li>
 <li>Hold the lancet device against the side of the fingertip and apply pressure. Press the release button to prick the finger. Dispose of the lancet in the Sharps container immediately.</li>
 <li>Gently squeeze the finger to produce a large drop of blood. Wipe away the first drop with gauze and discard in the biohazard container.</li>
 <li>Gently squeeze again until another drop appears. Place the meter next to the fingertip and touch the <strong>tip</strong> of the strip to the blood drop — blood wicks in automatically. Do not press the strip against skin or place blood on top of the strip.</li>
 <li>After a beep, the meter counts down 5 seconds and displays the result. Apply a bandage to the participant's fingertip.</li>
 <li>Record the result. Dispose of the test strip in the Sharps container.</li>
 </ol>

 <div class="section-title">Critical Result Thresholds</div>
 <div class="two-col">
 <div class="info-card">
 <div class="card-title" style="color:var(--usw-danger)">HI / &gt; 600 mg/dL</div>
 <p>Change gloves and repeat the test. If still reads HI, refer to emergency procedures and call <strong>866.881.7607</strong>.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="info-card">
 <div class="card-title" style="color:var(--usw-danger)">LO / &lt; 10 mg/dL</div>
 <p>Change gloves and repeat the test. If still reads LO, refer to emergency procedures and call <strong>866.881.7607</strong>.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="info-card">
 <div class="card-title" style="color:var(--usw-warn)">&gt; 250 mg/dL</div>
 <p>May indicate a potentially serious condition. Refer to talking points and emergency procedure.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="info-card">
 <div class="card-title" style="color:var(--usw-warn)">&lt; 50 mg/dL</div>
 <p>May indicate a potentially serious medical condition. Refer to talking points and emergency procedure.</p>
 </div>
 </div>

 <div class="section-title">Error Codes</div>
 <div class="troubleshoot-row"><div class="err">E1</div><div class="cause">Temperature out of range</div><div class="fix">Meter must be between 41–113°F. Move to an appropriate area and allow 20 minutes to adjust.</div></div>
 <div class="troubleshoot-row"><div class="err">E2</div><div class="cause">Insufficient blood</div><div class="fix">Strip did not fill enough. Dispose and retest with a new strip. Wait for the flashing blood drop before retesting.</div></div>
 <div class="troubleshoot-row"><div class="err">E3</div><div class="cause">Used test strip</div><div class="fix">Meter detected a used strip. Dispose and retest with a new strip.</div></div>
 <div class="troubleshoot-row"><div class="err">E4</div><div class="cause">Strip not inserted correctly</div><div class="fix">Remove and reinsert with the gray end facing up into the test strip port.</div></div>
 <div class="troubleshoot-row"><div class="err">E7</div><div class="cause">Incorrect sensor type</div><div class="fix">Remove and retest with a new strip. Confirm you are using a Bayer CONTOUR test strip.</div></div>
 <div class="troubleshoot-row"><div class="err">E11</div><div class="cause">Abnormal result</div><div class="fix">Remove and retest with a new strip. Call 866.881.7607 if E11 appears a second time.</div></div>
 <div class="troubleshoot-row"><div class="err">E5/E6/E8/E9/E12/E13</div><div class="cause">Software/hardware issue</div><div class="fix">Remove strip and reinsert with a new strip. Call 866.881.7607 if problem continues.</div></div>
 <div class="troubleshoot-row"><div class="err">🔋 Battery</div><div class="cause">Dead battery</div><div class="fix">Battery icon flashes for 10 seconds and meter turns off. Replace battery before continuing.</div></div>

