 <!-- MODULE 5c: BMI -->
 <div class="page" id="page-mod9">
 <div class="module-header">
 <div class="module-tag">Module 09</div>
 <h2>BMI</h2>
 <div class="desc">Body Mass Index — what it measures, what it doesn't, and how to counsel on results.</div>
 </div>

 <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:10px">BMI is calculated from measured height and weight only. It is not a direct measure of body fat — it is an elementary screening tool to identify possible weight problems in adults, not a diagnostic tool. Goal range: <strong>18.5 – 24.9</strong>. Every point on the BMI scale is approximately equal to 5 pounds.</p>
 <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:10px">Input of measured height and weight will yield the BMI in the patient record in Salesforce. BMI is visible on the results screen when height and weight are input.</p>

 <div class="section-title">How to Accurately Measure Height Using the Digital Height Wand</div>
 <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:10px">(Replaces stadiometer) Turn device on and ensure it is in inches mode (IN) — the "IN" will be lit up. If device is not in inches, hold the "person" icon button for 3 seconds to switch from meters to inches.</p>
 <ol class="sop-list">
 <li>Ask participant to stand against a flat wall (similar to where you would have set a stadiometer).</li>
 <li>Ensure the digital screen of the device is facing down. Hold device on top of person's head with circle base pressed against wall.</li>
 <li>Ask person to step out from under device. Press the "Person" icon to start measurement. When complete you will hear three beeps. Record the inches measurement shown into Salesforce (you will need to calculate feet and inches if using OPA).</li>
 </ol>

 <div class="section-title">Common Troubleshooting</div>
 <ul class="bullet-list">
 <li>Ensure participant stepped out from under device before the measurement starts. Ensure no other object is in the direct path of the beam from height wand to floor.</li>
 <li>Ensure clear plastic film is off the screen.</li>
 <li>Ensure digital screen of device is pointing down and not at the ceiling.</li>
 </ul>

 <div class="two-col">
 <div class="info-card">
 <div class="card-title">Underweight</div>
 <div class="card-val">&lt; 18.5</div>
 <p>Encourage follow-up with a physician.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="info-card">
 <div class="card-title">Normal</div>
 <div class="card-val">18.5 – 24.9</div>
 <p>Healthy range. Encourage maintaining current habits.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="info-card">
 <div class="card-title">Overweight</div>
 <div class="card-val">25.0 – 29.9</div>
 <p>Note elevated risk. Encourage physical activity and dietary improvements.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="info-card">
 <div class="card-title">Obese</div>
 <div class="card-val">≥ 30.0</div>
 <p>Higher risk for diabetes, heart disease, and hypertension. Recommend physician follow-up.</p>
 </div>
 </div>

