 <!-- MODULE 5d: COTININE -->
 <div class="page" id="page-mod10">
 <div class="module-header">
 <div class="module-tag">Module 10</div>
 <h2>Cotinine</h2>
 <div class="desc">Oral cotinine swab test procedure, timing, and result interpretation.</div>
 </div>

 <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">Cotinine is the major breakdown product of nicotine. This oral swab test is performed only when a participant indicates they are tobacco-free on the consent form.</p>

 <ol class="sop-list">
 <li>If participant indicates tobacco-free on consent form, perform the cotinine mouth swab test.</li>
 <li>Ask participant to insert the sponge end into their mouth and actively swab the inside of the mouth and tongue for at least <strong>3 minutes</strong>. Use a timer.</li>
 <li>Insert the collector vertically into the cap and press down firmly until the cap reaches the thread. Twist the handle clockwise 180° until the Red Arrow aligns with the white mark.</li>
 <li>Place the test device <strong>horizontally</strong> on a clean, level surface with the result window facing up.</li>
 <li>Read results at <strong>10 minutes</strong>. If results are invalid, repeat once.</li>
 </ol>

 <div class="callout info">
 <span class="callout-icon">ℹ️</span>
 <div><strong>Reading cotinine results:</strong> A <strong>positive</strong> result (cotinine detected) shows one line at C only. A <strong>negative</strong> result (no cotinine) shows lines at both C and COT. An <strong>invalid</strong> result shows no lines or only COT — repeat the test once.</div>
 </div>

