 <div class="page" id="page-mod13">
 <div class="module-header">
 <div class="module-tag">Module 13</div>
 <h2>Hardware &amp; Software Acceptable Use</h2>
 <div class="desc">USW policies governing the use of company-provided equipment, software, data, and communications systems.</div>
 </div>

 <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:16px">Hardware and software provided for your use in field operations — including but not limited to computer equipment, software, operating systems, storage media, and system accounts — are the property of USW. These systems are to be used only for USW-directed business purposes in serving the interests of USW and our clients and customers. This policy applies to all employees, contractors, consultants, business associates, and other workers including all personnel affiliated with third parties.</p>

 <div class="section-title">General Use &amp; Ownership</div>
 <ul class="bullet-list">
 <li>Hardware, software, and all data created in the course of directed business operations is the property of USW.</li>
 <li>Users must promptly return USW assets as directed.</li>
 <li>Authorized individuals within USW and its network management vendor(s) may monitor equipment, systems, and network traffic at any time.</li>
 </ul>

 <div class="section-title">Security &amp; Proprietary Information</div>
 <ul class="bullet-list">
 <li>All information, reports, deliverables, and materials generated by Users are classified as confidential intellectual property of US Wellness.</li>
 <li>Authorized users are responsible for the security of their passwords and accounts. Users are not permitted to share user logins or passwords.</li>
 <li>All information that constitutes protected health information (PHI) must only and always be accessed using USW-issued and/or approved computers.</li>
 </ul>

 <div class="section-title">Unacceptable Use — System &amp; Network Activities</div>
 <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:10px">The following activities are <strong>strictly prohibited</strong>, with no exceptions:</p>
 <ul class="bullet-list">
 <li>Installing or distributing software products that are not appropriately licensed for use by USW.</li>
 <li>Unauthorized copying of copyrighted material including photographs, music, or any software for which USW does not have an active license.</li>
 <li>Failure to promptly return USW assets as directed.</li>
 <li>Exporting software, technical information, or encryption technology in violation of export control laws.</li>
 <li>Introducing malicious programs into the network or server (e.g., viruses, worms, Trojan horses, email bombs).</li>
 <li>Revealing your account password to others or allowing use of your account by others — including family and household members when working from home.</li>
 <li>Using a USW computing asset to procure or transmit material that violates sexual harassment or hostile workplace laws.</li>
 <li>Making fraudulent offers of products, items, or services from any USW account.</li>
 <li>Making unauthorized statements about warranty, expressly or implied.</li>
 <li>Effecting security breaches or disruptions of network communication, including unauthorized access to data or servers, network sniffing, packet spoofing, denial of service, or forged routing information.</li>
 <li>Port scanning, security scanning, or any form of unauthorized network monitoring.</li>
 <li>Circumventing user authentication or security of any host, network, or account.</li>
 <li>Interfering with or denying service to any user or system.</li>
 <li>Using any program or command with intent to interfere with or disable a user's terminal session.</li>
 <li>Providing information about or lists of USW employees or users to parties outside USW.</li>
 </ul>

 <div class="section-title">Unacceptable Use — Email &amp; Communications</div>
 <ul class="bullet-list">
 <li>Sending unsolicited email (spam) or junk mail to USW clients or other users.</li>
 <li>Any form of harassment via email, telephone, or other messaging — whether through language, frequency, or message size.</li>
 <li>Unauthorized use or forging of email sender or header information.</li>
 <li>Posting non-business-related messages to large numbers of newsgroups or distribution lists.</li>
 </ul>

 <div class="callout danger">
 <span class="callout-icon">⚠️</span>
 <div><strong>Enforcement</strong> Any User found to have violated this policy may be subject to disciplinary action, up to and including termination of employment, vendor, or contractor status. Legal action will be taken when actions are unlawful or in violation of this agreement.</div>
 </div>

 <div class="section-title">Clean Desk / Clean Screen Policy</div>
 <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">An effective clean desk effort protects digital and paper documents containing sensitive information about our clients, customers, and vendors. All employees must maintain mandatory compliance.</p>
 <ul class="bullet-list">
 <li>When working at home or remotely, sensitive information may not be visible or accessible on screen at any time.</li>
 <li>Sensitive data may not be removed from USW offices at any time.</li>
 <li>Sensitive data may not be printed without express written authorization by the Privacy Officer.</li>
 <li>At the end of the working day, tidy your desk and put away all office papers in a secure area that cannot be accessed by others.</li>
 <li>Always clear your workspace before leaving for longer periods of time.</li>
