 <!-- MODULE 13: HIPAA & PRIVACY -->
 <div class="page" id="page-mod14">
 <div class="module-header">
 <div class="module-tag">Module 14</div>
 <h2>HIPAA &amp; Privacy</h2>
 <div class="desc">Annual HIPAA training covering PHI protections, security responsibilities, password management, and compliance standards for all US Wellness staff.</div>
 </div>

 <div class="section-title">What is HIPAA?</div>
 <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px">HIPAA (Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act) establishes national standards for protecting sensitive patient health information. US Wellness operates as a <strong>Business Associate</strong> — we access and process Protected Health Information (PHI) on behalf of Covered Entities (health care providers, insurance companies, and healthcare clearinghouses). A Business Associate Agreement (BAA) governs this relationship.</p>

 <div class="section-title">Protected Health Information (PHI)</div>
 <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:10px">PHI is any health information tied to an individual identifier. The following are protected <strong>when linked to health information</strong>:</p>
 <ul class="bullet-list">
 <li>Name, address, city, county, zip code</li>
 <li>Dates (birth, admission, discharge, death)</li>
 <li>Social Security Number, Medical Record Number, Health Plan Member ID</li>
 <li>Account numbers, certificate or license numbers</li>
 <li>Vehicle ID or serial numbers, including license plates</li>
 <li>Face images and contact info (phone, email)</li>
 </ul>
 <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;margin:10px 0 12px 0">HIPAA's <strong>Security Rule</strong> requires safeguarding PHI in all forms — electronic, verbal, and paper. The <strong>Privacy Rule</strong> prohibits unauthorized disclosure of PHI.</p>

 <div class="section-title">PHI Data Sharing Protocols</div>
 <ul class="bullet-list">
 <li>A Data Sharing Agreement and/or BAA must be in place with any entity that will receive PHI.</li>
 <li>Data is only exported or prepared by the USW Data Science team and sent via USW's Managed File Transfer (MFT) system or a designated SFTP site.</li>
 <li>Export files and all derivatives are deleted from all sources except Salesforce after export.</li>
 <li>Participation reports sent to third parties must contain no PHI, no date of birth, and no filters that could identify individuals.</li>
 </ul>

 <div class="section-title">Your Security Responsibilities</div>
 <ul class="bullet-list">
 <li>Complete all required trainings (monthly).</li>
 <li>Do not copy, export, or distribute PHI from company systems outside of US Wellness.</li>
 <li>Notify and block phishing and other malicious attempts.</li>
 <li>Maintain privacy of your username and password at all times.</li>
 <li>Access authorized PHI only on company-issued, approved, and encrypted devices using multifactor authentication.</li>
 <li>Use the Virtual Private Network (VPN) when required.</li>
 <li>Comply with the Clean Desk Policy (see Module 12).</li>
 </ul>

 <div class="section-title">Clean Desk / Screen / Workstation</div>
 <ul class="bullet-list">
 <li>Sensitive information may not be visible or accessible on screen to others — including during screen sharing, at home, while traveling, or at remote work locations (coffee shops, gyms, etc.).</li>
 <li>Sensitive data may not be copied, exported, printed, downloaded, emailed, or transmitted without express authorization.</li>
 <li>Put away all company materials so others cannot access them.</li>
 <li>Lock your device when away for any period of time (Control + Alt + Delete → Lock).</li>
 <li>Log out of all systems and applications at end of day.</li>
 </ul>

 <div class="section-title">Password Management</div>
 <ul class="bullet-list">
 <li>Use strong passwords and treat them as sensitive, confidential information.</li>
 <li>Do not disclose your login or password to any individual, inside or outside the company, for any reason.</li>
 <li>Do not write down or store passwords insecurely.</li>
 <li>Do not reveal your password during screen sharing, in email, chat, or any other electronic communication.</li>
 <li>Report improper use of passwords immediately to the Privacy Officer at <strong>privacy@uswellness.com</strong>.</li>
 <li>If an account or password compromise is suspected, report it to the Privacy Officer immediately.</li>
 </ul>

 <div class="section-title">At Events — PHI Reminders</div>
 <ul class="bullet-list">
 <li><strong>At events:</strong> Maintain privacy and security of paper forms, tablet screens, and logins at all times.</li>
 <li><strong>In meetings:</strong> Keep your screen clean — no PHI visible to others.</li>
 <li><strong>Logged into USW systems:</strong> Do not access PHI on your personal phone or non-USW device. No downloading, printing, copying, screenshotting, or exporting of PHI or sensitive information.</li>
 </ul>

 <div class="callout danger">
 <span class="callout-icon">🔒</span>
 <div><strong>Report all suspicious activity</strong> Contact the USW Privacy Team immediately for any inappropriate or questionable activity.<br><br>
 <a href="mailto:privacy@uswellness.com" style="color:var(--usw-red)">privacy@uswellness.com</a></div>
 </div>

